{
  "texts": [
    "While technology has made significant strides in combating cryptocurrency money laundering, ongoing research and development are needed to address these challenges (Dupuis and Gleason, 2020).",
    "This will enhance the effectiveness of anti-money laundering efforts in the cryptocurrency space.",
    "The exploration of new AML strategies is driven by the need for agile and adaptive approaches to detection and prevention (Han et al., 2020).",
    "In this regard, the emergence of novel machine learning techniques, which have demonstrated the ability to analyze vast amounts of data and identify patterns indicative of illicit activities, significantly bolstered AML efforts (Chen et al., 2018).",
    "Therefore, emerging AML dynamics have led to a notable shift towards the exploration of artificial intelligence (AI) technologies within the AML domain."
  ]
}